            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  Angle-integrated relative line intensity",
                "from fits of the gamma-ray angular distributions of the",
                " Ep = 1747 keV resonance of the 13C(p,gamma) reaction.",
                "The angular distribution of the 3338 KeV gamma rays has",
                "been fitted with two different assumptions for the",
                "transition multipolarity L=1 and L=2 (E1 or M2 for the",
                "2+ -> 3- transition).  Normally, this should be only",
                " E1, however, we included the results of the fit with",
                " L=2 into the table, because the a4 parameter was not",
                "compatible with zero.  We prefer still the value for",
                " L=1, that's why we put parenthesis (3338) for the l=2",
                "result.  Sorry, we did not explain in the text of the",
                "paper."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The uncertainty includes a contribution due",
                "to a0 and an additional contribution of 5% which",
                "accounts for the uncertainty of the detector efficiency",
                "curve for lines other than the 9169 KeV line."
              ]
            }
          ],
